Quote:  in battle, each chief always carried a staff of very hard wood with a carved head, the sharp point of which, designed to resemble a human tongue thrust out in defiance, was urged forward as a mark of insult to the enemy; ... This staff, called `e haui,' was also carried in the cirle of debate; ...
